.TH GIT-ABSORB-AND-REBASE 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-absorb-and-rebase \- absorb staged changes into earlier commits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git absorb-and-rebase
.RB [ \-b | \-\-base
.IR rev ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git absorb-and-rebase
creates git-absorb fixup commits for staged changes on the current branch, then
folds those fixups with a non-interactive autosquash rebase.
.PP
The command operates only on staged changes. It refuses active
rebase, merge, cherry-pick, or revert states, and rolls back partial fixup
generation if git-absorb leaves staged changes behind.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-base " " \fIrev\fR
Rebase from this base revision instead of deriving one.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH BASE SELECTION
When no base is given, the command derives one from the branch upstream,
remote default branches such as
.BR origin/HEAD ,
.BR origin/main ,
or
.BR origin/master ,
then local default branches such as
.BR main ,
.BR master ,
or
.BR trunk .
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.B git-absorb
must be installed.
